HEADWORD: Geropigia
<hw>Ger`o*pig"i*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pg.
<ets>geropiga</ets>.]</ety> <def>A mixture composed of unfermented grape
juice, brandy, sugar, etc., for adulteration of wines.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>jerupigia</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>-gerous</ent>⟦br⟧
